~Chloride influx
}

::synapse_synaptic_vesicles::
Synaptic vesicles are best described as:
{
~Ion channels
=Membrane-bound organelles storing neurotransmitters #Synaptic vesicles store neurotransmitters at high concentration.
~Receptors on the postsynaptic membrane
~Mitochondria at synapses
}

::synapse_neurotransmitter_release::
Neurotransmitter release is described as quantal because:
{
~It is continuous
=It occurs in discrete packets #Release occurs in discrete vesicle fusion events.
~It depends on ion diffusion only
~It is electrically graded
}

::synapse_which_proteins::
Which proteins mediate vesicle fusion?
{
~Ion channels
~G-proteins
=SNARE proteins #SNARE proteins bring vesicle and membrane together for fusion.
~Transporters
}

::synapse_neurotransmitter_release::
Neurotransmitter release occurs through:
{
~Endocytosis
