=Exocytosis #Vesicles release neurotransmitters by exocytosis.
~Active transport
}

::synapse_postsynaptic_receptors::
Postsynaptic receptors are located on the:
{
~Presynaptic terminal
~Synaptic cleft
=Postsynaptic membrane #Receptors are embedded in the postsynaptic membrane.
~Axon initial segment
}

::synapse_ionotropic_receptors::
Ionotropic receptors are characterized by:
{
~Slow modulatory effects
~G-protein activation
=Ligand-gated ion channels #Ionotropic receptors directly open ion channels upon binding.
~Second messenger cascades
}

::synapse_metabotropic_receptors::
Metabotropic receptors differ from ionotropic receptors because they:
{
~Form ion channels
