=Activate intracellular signaling pathways #Metabotropic receptors act via G-proteins and signaling cascades.
~Produce only fast responses
}

::synapse_epsps_are::
EPSPs are typically produced by:
{
~Cl⁻ influx
=Na⁺ influx #Excitatory synapses usually depolarize the membrane via Na⁺ influx.
~K⁺ efflux only
~Na⁺ efflux
}

::synapse_ipsps_are::
IPSPs are commonly mediated by:
{
~Na⁺ influx
~Ca²⁺ influx
=Cl⁻ influx #Inhibitory synapses often involve Cl⁻ influx.
~Na⁺ efflux
}

