{
~Stressful environments
~Socially deprived conditions
=Enriched environments #Environment determines plastic outcomes.
~Isolated cages
}

::epigenetics_meaney_s::
Meaney’s studies showed that maternal care influences:
{
~DNA sequence
=Epigenetic regulation of stress-related genes #Maternal behavior programs stress systems.
~Brain size
~Motor development
}

::epigenetics_differences_between::
Differences between high- and low-nurturing mothers lie mainly in:
{
~Nutrition
~Abuse
=Quality of interaction #Basic care is normal in both groups.
~Genetic background
}

::epigenetics_high_maternal::
High maternal care leads to offspring with:
{
~Chronically active HPA axis
~Higher anxiety
=Better stress regulation #Stress responses are efficiently regulated.
~Lower glucocorticoid receptors
}

::epigenetics_glucocorticoid_receptors::
Glucocorticoid receptors in the hippocampus are important because they:
{
~Activate stress responses
